The paper deals with biometric authentication using mobile devices and focuses on image processing techniques for iris recognition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of matching software, which falls under the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also deals with security and privacy concerns, which are relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The study involves human subjects, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of selective RGB channel choice, which is a signal processing technique that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
